Sentencas: The development of alternative ceramic anodes for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells (LT-SOFCs) is essential to overcome the inherent challenges such as redox instability and coking associated with Ni-based cermet anodes.
Titulo: High Performance SrFe0.2Co0.4Mo0.4O3-δ Ceramic Anode Supported Low-Temperature SOFCs

Sentencas: Moreover, due to the large electrolyte ohmic loss at low temperature, it is critical to developing an electrode supported cell that allows electrolyte thickness reduction.
Titulo: High Performance SrFe0.2Co0.4Mo0.4O3-δ Ceramic Anode Supported Low-Temperature SOFCs

Sentencas: Here we successfully demonstrated a high performance SrFe0.2Co0.4Mo0.4O3-delta (SFCM) ceramic anode supported LT-SOFC with a peak power density of 730 mW cm(-2) and 300 mW cm(-2) at ambitious low temperatures of 550 degrees C and 450 degrees C, respectively, in humidified H-2.
Titulo: High Performance SrFe0.2Co0.4Mo0.4O3-δ Ceramic Anode Supported Low-Temperature SOFCs

Sentencas: The new anode material SFCM exhibits exceptional conductivity of over 30 S cm(-1) at 450 degrees C in humidified H-2, providing essential current collection capability as an anode backbone appropriate for the infiltration of Ni-gadolinia doped ceria (GDC) electrocatalysts.
Titulo: High Performance SrFe0.2Co0.4Mo0.4O3-δ Ceramic Anode Supported Low-Temperature SOFCs

Sentencas: Compared to conventional Ni-cermet anodes, the nano-sized Ni-GDC particles in our SFCM based electrode significantly improves the cell stability in hydrocarbon gases.
Titulo: High Performance SrFe0.2Co0.4Mo0.4O3-δ Ceramic Anode Supported Low-Temperature SOFCs

Sentencas: We demonstrated a stable long-term operation over a period of 380 h in CH4-containing gas mixtures at 450 degrees C with a voltage degradation rate of 4% per 1000 h at a constant current of 0.2 A*cm(-2).
Titulo: High Performance SrFe0.2Co0.4Mo0.4O3-δ Ceramic Anode Supported Low-Temperature SOFCs

Sentencas: Our results demonstrate a high performance ceramic anode with high stability for low temperature operation.
Titulo: High Performance SrFe0.2Co0.4Mo0.4O3-δ Ceramic Anode Supported Low-Temperature SOFCs
